comment:
* An event describing a keyboard interaction originating from a remote device.
 *
 * When the user presses a key, an {@code ACTION_DOWN} event should be reported. When the user
 * releases the key, an {@code ACTION_UP} event should be reported.
 *
 * See {@link android.view.KeyEvent}.
 *
 * @hide

variables.name: ACTION_DOWN
variables.comment: Action indicating the given key has been pressed.

variables.name: ACTION_UP
variables.comment: Action indicating the previously pressed key has been lifted.

methods.name: public void writeToParcel(@NonNull Parcel parcel, int parcelableFlags)
public int getKeyCode()
methods.comment: * Returns the key code associated with this event.

methods.name: public int getAction()
methods.comment: * Returns the action associated with this event.

methods.name: public long getEventTimeNanos()
methods.comment:
* Returns the time this event occurred, in the {@link SystemClock#uptimeMillis()} time base but
     * with nanosecond (instead of millisecond) precision.
     *
     * @see InputEvent#getEventTime()

methodNames: public void writeToParcel(@NonNull Parcel parcel, int parcelableFlags)
